This paper discusses the development of natural language models for chat-based dialog systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of data-driven and rule-based models also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The user study aspect of the paper suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC), while the evaluation of machine translation technology suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
